[section,expanded=Sunderance Act 2 - Chapter 05 - Pages 28-31]
Where to even begin about this last month. I know I like to throw a joke here and there but honestly this will be one of those months that I might get a little real. I've had a few extra expenses, from dentists, to large propane tanks, and bills getting more expensive. I had to resort to getting some extra cash via coms and even then I'm not totally recovered.

Among other delays, the pages got set back more than usual. I want to work on more Sunderance projects (we have a side story about Jack and Neveen and how they met, to get to) But thing being what they are, there is no sustainable model to get these projects rolling. My plate is once again full, which takes away not only my ability to work on the side projects but Sunderance itself.

Monthly updates are going to be difficult if we don't figure out a way to be a little more on sustainable. If you are reading this from Patreon then there really is nothing else you have to do and I appreciate all the support everyone has given us over the time I've taken up the mantle of artist. But now my computer has given me a few scares and the truth is, it's an old thing that needs a few upgrades. If I can't get on that soon, then if the thing breaks down, that's it for me.

I'm going to give out my ko-fi link for those of you out in the external websites to help me get some funds to start looking into new parts, it's looking to be MB; CPU and RAM, and I guess at this rate I might as well buy a whole new PC. I hate to e-beg but every little bit helps and I ask that you only help if you want to and it is in your ability to do so.
https://ko-fi.com/rickarts
-Rick

These pages are love. From Nick and Judy getting closer, to Zira being totally not evil in this comic, to Fin hiding his worry for all of them behind business. Seems about right. ;)
This part of the chapter is coming to a close, followed by the end of the chapter which is pretty short. And following this chapter, I will start posting story clips to go with the pages to ensure that those who think a thousand words is worth a picture will be happy.
Don't forget to donate! See you next time!
-Kulkum

[section,expanded=Sunderance Act 2 - Chapter 05 - Pages 24 to 27]
And here we have the latest update at last. Things have been busy at work, which is a thing one must do to survive, but Rick and I managed to push onward and give Zira her first look at the ever mysterious Jack.
There is a wild buck under all that calm. Hm...
I'm going to start posting Rick's sketches on Patreon when he is finished with them, to prevent it taking so long for updates to post. Sound good? :)
Also in the future, with the start of the next chapter, I will be posting story updates at quarter points in the story, also to avoid making people who are interested in my writing from waiting forever for it.
Donate if you can! We've dropped again... We are hoping that Zootopia 2 will return interest to the project, as well as the changes to updates.

-Kulkum


It was my birthday on the 28th. Birthday months are so chaotic.

In other news got ghosted after drafting a commission. It happens a lot more often than not, but it still sucks every time.

Well, at least the pages got done, ready to start work on the next batch, see you next update.
-Rick

If there's one character I deeply, DEEPLY regret not having made any fan art of for the longest time, it's Judy Hopps from Zootopia! I really don't know why I haven't, because like many people I find her to be such a lovable little bunny! Well, I'm gonna make an effort to fix that by making more fan art of her (as well as Nick for that matter) going forward. And so, for my first fan art I thought I'd start with something mostly simple yet wholesome, with Judy's little sister Molly giving her a popsicle that she got (more specifically their mother Bonnie got for her since Molly's still a toddler and all that) at the nearest ice cream parlor.

h4.Zootopia Day 2024

Happy Zootopia Day! 8th Anniversary and Z2 just around the corner!!!

ORIGINALLY UPLOADED FEBRUARY 2, 2024

When Judy Entered the Zootopia PD, she didn't thought she would be meeting with an old flame, an oddly creamy mud pit...Ok, that's my headcannon, but i don't care! This pic is a collab I made with my friend sirinathehedgehog. This is a comic that came to mind based on an idea I had for a fic from another fandom where it would show what it would be like if the characters of a fandom x lived in a tribal environment. Also, this is a crossover comic between Sonic The Hedgehog, Star Fox, Happy Tree Friends, Zootopia, Aggretsuko, Beastars, and BNA Brand New Animal. Although there are other fandoms included here. This is the twelfth page.



Returning to the current timeline, the main characters are doing several different activities with some members of their respective tribes.

Panel 1:
Sonic, Amy and Roxanne are collecting wood for the bonfire that will be made when the meal is prepared that night.

Panel 2:
Falco is angry because the spear he gave to Fox broke (he's not angry at Fox, but at himself for not making a stronger spear) Fox is trying to calm him down while Mangle repairs the spear (since she is very skilled at these things)

Panel 3:
Flippy and Flaky, while resting next to a river, watch as Foxy is fishing in an area near them, and unlike the other fishermen, he uses his own hands to catch the fish.

Panel 4:
While they are having a little lunch; Nick, Judy and Jack meet up with Bonnie and talk. Jack is surprised by Bonnie's size.

Panel 5:
Haida, Retsuko and Freddy decide to spend some time making music. With Haida playing a string instrument that he built for himself, Retsuko playing the flute that Haida gave her, while Freddy sings.

Panel 6:
Legoshi and Monty have had a pretty bad first meeting, which seems to be the beginning of a kind of rivalry while on the other hand Louis and Jack observe Monty with different reactions (Louis upset by how Monty treats Legoshi, while Jack for what Monty could do to Legoshi)

Panel 7:
Shirou and Michiru are talking with Chica, and she tells them about her desire to be a mother, representing that with a toy that belonged to her since she was little. Shirou, unknowingly, this causes Michiru to start having certain thoughts between her and him.


Main Couples:
Sonic x Amy / Sonamy
Falco x Fox / Falox
Flippy x Flaky
Nick x Judy x Jack / Wildehopps, Savagehopps, Wildehoppssavage
Haida x Retsuko / Haidsuko, Haisuko, Retsaida
Louis x Legoshi x Jack
Shirou x Michiru

Secondary Couples that appeared before this page:
Paulie x Brenda
James x Vixy
Peppy x Slippy
Sneaky x Mouse Ka-Boom
Disco Bear x Pop
Stu x Bonnie
Bucky x Pronk
Retsuko's father x Retsuko's mother
Yafya x Gosha
Tao x Kibi
Gem x Melissa



Note 1: As you can see, of the classic Five Night's At Freddy's characters in this comic, only Bonnie maintains his classic designs, Foxy has his design from Bear of Vengeance shorts (although without the hook), while Freddy and Chica have their Glamrock designs. The reason Bonnie doesn't have his Glamock desing here is because this page was made months before Five Night's At Freddy's Security Breach - Ruin came out and it would be a lot of work to redo the page, which was already colored when the game's DLC was released.

Note 2: Mangle has the design that most fans give her appearance prior to her destruction. Although here the red and pink parts of her coat are part of her birth fur and not body paint.

Note 3: The light blue and red parts of Freddy's fur, the pink parts of Chica's plumage, the black parts of Roxanne's fur and green parts of her hair, and the purple parts of Monty's scales here are from birth and it isn't body paint either.

Note 4: The toy that Chica holds in her hands is intended to represent her classic design.

Note 5: This page was originally supposed to have been posted on Sunday of last week, but since the Five Nights At Freddy's movie was going to be released this week, I decided to wait until the movie was released to post this.

Here's a commission I recently wrapped for Gabriel LaVedier feature a lovely PredxPrey pairing, and with Sharla's brother no less. Not sure if there's a full fic associated with this, but there is some background info.

Garreth is, as you know, Sharla's brother. His last name is Ovine in this AU. Garreth as an adult is fairly mild mannered and clean cut, keeping his horns on the small side so no one thinks he's looking for a fight. He works the family farm, and unlike Sharla, stuck with the family business (Although Sharla came back to town). He also is in charge of hiring on the help, of which Gisela is picked up to do farmwork at the Ovine family farm.

Gisela is looking for a new start. Essentially leaving Zootopia with her motorcycle and the clothes on her back to get away from the trauma her family has experienced living in Zootopia. With her two other siblings in prison, which is implied to be a betrayal of the system as her brother was a solider and her sister worked with him at his personal protection company, it seems Gisela feels equally lied to by Zootopia's promises of equality.

If it's not clear by the image, the pair catch feelings, and in this specific image, Gisela seems to be looking to leave the Burrows, and Garreth is making his case for her to say as the pair seem to be inadvertently inching their muzzles closer and closer.
